<h3>The Instagram-to-Website Pipeline</h3>
<p>Do not choose between Instagram and your website. Use both strategically.</p>
<p>Instagram drives discovery. Your website converts that discovery into bookings. The pipeline works like this:</p>
<ol>
<li>Client sees your work on Instagram</li>
<li>Client searches your shop name on Google</li>
<li>Client lands on your website, browses your portfolio, reads reviews</li>
<li>Client books through your online booking system</li>
</ol>
<p>Your website needs to be the strongest link in that chain. Clean design, fast load speed, mobile-friendly, and easy booking.</p>
<h3>Online Booking: The Revenue Multiplier</h3>
<p><a href="https://agentzap.ai/blog/tattoo-shop-phone-statistics">62% of tattoo inquiries happen outside business hours</a>. Peak inquiry time is 7 to 9 PM. If your shop only takes bookings by phone during business hours, you lose the majority of potential clients.</p>
<p>An online booking system with deposit collection solves 2 problems at once. It captures after-hours inquiries and reduces no-shows. Without deposits, no-show rates run 20% to 30%. With deposits, they drop to 2% to 8%. That alone can add $500 to $1,000 per week in recovered revenue for a busy shop.</p>
<p>Add a booking button to every page of your website, your GBP listing, and your Instagram bio.</p>
