<p>Most tattoo shop websites prioritize aesthetics over structure. Dark themes, full-screen images, minimal text. Beautiful to look at. Invisible to Google.</p>
<h3>The Tattoo Shop On-Page Checklist</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Title tags include style, service, and city ("Japanese Tattoo Artist Austin TX | [Shop Name]")</li>
<li>[ ] Meta descriptions describe your specialty and location (145 to 155 characters)</li>
<li>[ ] H1 tag on every page matches the topic</li>
<li>[ ] Artist pages include name, specialties, bio, and portfolio</li>
<li>[ ] Style pages include descriptions, examples, and pricing ranges</li>
<li>[ ] <a href="/blog/on-page-seo-guide/">Schema markup</a> with LocalBusiness type (use TattooParlor subtype if available)</li>
<li>[ ] Mobile-responsive design (most tattoo clients browse on phones)</li>
<li>[ ] Page loads under 3 seconds (compress portfolio images)</li>
<li>[ ] NAP (Name, Address, Phone) in the footer of every page</li>
<li>[ ] Online booking button visible on every page</li>
</ul>
